variable "mtls_truststore_version" {
  type        = string
  description = "S3 object version ID of the mTLS truststore. Required when the truststore content is updated so AWS knows exactly which version to trust."
  default     = null
}



dynamic "mutual_tls_authentication" { 
  for_each = var.mtls_truststore_uri != null ? [1] : [] 
  content { 
    truststore_uri     = var.mtls_truststore_uri
    truststore_version = var.mtls_truststore_version
  } 
}


mtls_truststore_version = "PASTE_THE_VERSION_ID_HERE"



/explain Unexpected attribute: An attribute named "mtls_truststore_version" is not expected here

The error means mtls_truststore_version is placed in a block that does not support it.

This attribute belongs inside the mutual_tls_authentication block, not at the top level of the resource.

Fix — nest it correctly
Note: The argument is truststore_version, not mtls_truststore_version. The mtls_ prefix is not part of the HCL schema — it is just the parent block name.

